==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harl
<hw>Harl</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rl)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OHG.
<ets>harluf</ets> noose, rope; E. <ets>hards</ets> refuse of
flax.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A filamentous substance; especially, the
filaments of flax or hemp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A barb, or barbs, of a fine large feather, as of a
peacock or ostrich, -- used in dressing artificial flies.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>herl</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harle</ent>⟦br⟧
